rComments: One of the best profs! Totally recommend. His lectures are clear, and answers question whenever
Great prof and very caring. Always willing to help. Overall a great guy
He's just awesome. He cares, he explains well, he makes sure we're ready for exam... I recommend!

Prof Fomatati takes his time to explain (and sometimes reexplain) in order for his students to understand. Always accessible and does his very best to help his students. Midterms reflect what is taught in class and are quite easy if you study for it. Overall an excellent professor

Prof Yves truly cares about his students, he is always accessible outside class and does his best to help you. The tests reflected what was taught and the notes on Brightspace are so good that you dont even have to attend lectures ( but I recommend attending dgds as they reflect whats on the tests ) This course is an easy A+ if you work for it

Très bon prof. Ses cours sont très claires et surtout complets. Explique bien le contenu du cours et prends le temps d'aider les élèves qui éprouvent des difficultés. Les examens reflètent ce qu'on a vu avec lui en classe. Faites les exercices qu'il vous demande de faire, que ça soit ceux du livre ou du cours et vous aurez une bonne note.

Pros : -Sweet and caring personality -Carefully structured and well-organized course notes/reviews (helpful as far as test prep' is concerned) -Easy quizzes -Fair tests with a good allocation of points Cons : -Disorganized and confusing pedagogical approach during lectures (expect a strong reliance on external resources to fully grasp concepts)

One of the best teacher i have this fall. You can always reach him if you have a problem. He always answered my mails and was really comprehensive about online class's matters. _ Je pense que j'ai vraiment de la chance de l'avoir comme professeur pour ma première année . Sa meilleure qualité selon moi est sa disponibilité.

Probably the worst teacher I've had in my 3 years. He is scatterbrain when trying to explain things and makes you rewrite all the notes that are already online, so you don't really learn anything new. I've been to 3 classes, got confused and taught myself the rest from online videos. He also doesn't answer your questions properly/at all in emails.
